title: Sample Book (Japan), 19th century
description: Twenty-four double leaves, uncut, on the outer pages of which are mounted rectangles of silk with stencil-resist patterns, six to a page. First leaf marbled in red, blue and gray and inscribed. Patterns labeled in Japanese. Impressed cardboard cover, green silk thread binding.

tombstone.epitaph: Sample Book (Japan), 19th century; silk samples, paper book; H x W: 19 x 26 cm (7 1/2 x 10 1/4 in.); Gift of Rowland Burdon-Muller; 1939-17-5
